WHAT

gserial is a library for serial port communications. You could use it to talk
to Arduinos and other things. 

gserial is written in C using the GLib Object System (GObject). 

WHY

Before gserial it was very difficult, maybe even impossible, to use a serial 
port in Vala and GJS across Linux and Windows operating systems. gserial makes 
it very easy. 


